Normally, the request for a disability benefit is submitted by your employing organization. However, if you were separated from service or were placed on leave without pay for reasons of health after having exhausted your paid leave entitlements (sick leave on full pay, sick leave on half pay and annual leave), and you believe you were disabled at the time of your separation or at the time that you were placed on leave without pay, you may submit a request directly to the Secretary of the Staff Pension Committee of your employing organization in accordance with Sections H.4 and H.5 of the Fund's Administrative Rules. In order for you to make a request directly to the Secretary of your Staff Pension Committee, all of the following conditions must be met:
a. Your employing organization did not submit your case for determination by the Staff Pension Committee;
b. You did not separate from service pursuant to an agreed termination with your employing organization;
c. No payment has yet been made to you by the Fund;
d. You have fully exhausted all paid leave entitlements (sick leave with full pay, sick leave with half pay, annual leave);
e. You have exhausted any applicable administrative recourse against your employing organization under the applicable Staff Regulations and Rules; and
f. You made your request within four months of separation or the commencement of your leave without pay.
